Here’s a complete, self-contained, mobile‑responsive HTML page based on the infographic, with a few cleaned‑up details (for example, clarifying current Gemini / Workspace naming and tightening some wording).

You can save this as `teachers-guide-google-ai.html` and open it in any browser.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>Teacher’s Guide to Free Google AI Tools</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg-page: #f3f4f6;
      --bg-card: #ffffff;
      --text-main: #111827;
      --text-muted: #4b5563;
      --border-soft: #e5e7eb;

      --green-light: #e6f6ec;
      --green-strong: #16a34a;

      --yellow-light: #fff7d6;
      --yellow-strong: #eab308;

      --orange-light: #ffe6d8;
      --orange-strong: #f97316;

      --purple-light: #f2e7ff;
      --purple-strong: #8b5cf6;

      --accent-blue: #2563eb;
      --radius-lg: 16px;
      --shadow-soft: 0 18px 45px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.12);
      --shadow-light: 0 8px 20px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.08);
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    html, body {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      scroll-behavior: smooth;
    }

    body {
      font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI",
        sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.5;
      background: radial-gradient(circle at top left, #e0f2fe, #f3e8ff 35%, #f3f4f6 70%);
      color: var(--text-main);
    }

    a {
      color: var(--accent-blue);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    a:hover,
    a:focus-visible {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    .page {
      max-width: 1200px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 1.5rem 1.25rem 3rem;
    }

    header.hero {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #111827, #1e293b);
      color: #f9fafb;
      padding: 1.75rem 1.5rem 1.75rem;
      border-radius: 24px;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
      margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
    }

    header.hero::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      inset: -60%;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at 0 0, rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.24), transparent 55%),
        radial-gradient(circle at 100% 0, rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.2), transparent 55%),
        radial-gradient(circle at 100% 100%, rgba(244, 114, 182, 0.18), transparent 55%);
      opacity: 0.7;
      pointer-events: none;
    }

    .hero-inner {
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 3fr) minmax(0, 2.4fr);
      gap: 1.75rem;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .hero-eyebrow {
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      padding: 0.15rem 0.55rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background-color: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.65);
      border: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.6);
    }

    .hero-eyebrow span.dot {
      width: 0.4rem;
      height: 0.4rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: #22c55e;
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 4px rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.4);
    }

    .hero-title {
      margin: 0.35rem 0 0.5rem;
      font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 3vw + 0.7rem, 2.6rem);
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    }

    .hero-subtitle {
      margin: 0.35rem 0 0.9rem;
      font-size: 0.98rem;
      color: #e5e7eb;
      max-width: 34rem;
    }

    .hero-subtitle strong {
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .hero-disclaimer {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 0.86rem;
      color: #cbd5f5;
    }

    .hero-disclaimer strong {
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .hero-disclaimer code {
      font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas,
        "Liberation Mono", "Courier New", monospace;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.7);
      padding: 0.08rem 0.35rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
    }

    .hero-chip {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      padding: 0.4rem 0.75rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.7);
      color: #e5e7eb;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
    }

    .hero-chip span.icon {
      width: 1.35rem;
      height: 1.35rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      background: radial-gradient(circle, #22c55e, #16a34a);
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 4px rgba(22, 163, 74, 0.35);
      font-size: 0.85rem;
    }

    .hero-chip small {
      opacity: 0.9;
    }

    nav.section-nav {
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
      margin-top: 1.2rem;
      background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.7);
      padding: 0.55rem 0.6rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.75);
      overflow-x: auto;
      -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
    }

    nav.section-nav ul {
      list-style: none;
      display: flex;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 0;
      white-space: nowrap;
    }

    nav.section-nav a {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.35rem;
      padding: 0.3rem 0.85rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: #e5e7eb;
      text-decoration: none;
      border: 1px solid transparent;
    }

    nav.section-nav a span.emoji {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    nav.section-nav a:hover,
    nav.section-nav a:focus-visible {
      background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.95);
      border-color: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.9);
    }

    nav.section-nav a.is-primary {
      background: #facc15;
      color: #1f2937;
      border-color: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.12);
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.12);
    }

    nav.section-nav a.is-primary .emoji {
      filter: saturate(1.3);
    }

    /* Getting started cards */

    section#getting-started {
      margin: 2rem 0 2.5rem;
    }

    section#getting-started > h2 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
    }

    section#getting-started > p {
      margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      max-width: 40rem;
    }

    .tool-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 1.25rem;
    }

    .tool-card {
      background: rgba(248, 250, 252, 0.98);
      border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      padding: 1rem 1.1rem 1.1rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--border-soft);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-light);
      backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    }

    .tool-card h3 {
      margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
      font-size: 1.02rem;
      display: flex;
      align-items: baseline;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .tool-card .tool-chip {
      border-radius: 999px;
      padding: 0.1rem 0.5rem;
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      border: 1px solid rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.12);
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
      color: #6b7280;
    }

    .tool-url {
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
      color: #6b7280;
    }

    .tool-url a {
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    .tool-card p {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
    }

    .tool-tagline {
      margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
      font-weight: 500;
      color: #111827;
    }

    .tool-card ul {
      margin: 0.15rem 0 0;
      padding-left: 1.1rem;
      font-size: 0.86rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
    }

    .tool-card li + li {
      margin-top: 0.1rem;
    }

    /* Teaching sections */

    .teaching-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 1.5rem;
      align-items: stretch;
    }

    .teaching-section {
      border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      padding: 1.25rem 1.25rem 1.4rem;
      background: var(--bg-card);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-light);
      border-top: 4px solid transparent;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .teaching-section::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      inset: -1px;
      opacity: 0.7;
      pointer-events: none;
      background: radial-gradient(circle at 0 0, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9), transparent 53%);
    }

    .teaching-section-inner {
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
    }

    .teaching-section h2 {
      margin: 0 0 0.1rem;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      display: flex;
      align-items: baseline;
      gap: 0.45rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .teaching-section h2 span.emoji {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }

    .teaching-section .section-label {
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }

    .section-tagline {
      margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
    }

    .tool-block {
      margin-top: 0.8rem;
      padding: 0.75rem 0.85rem 0.85rem;
      border-radius: 10px;
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
      border: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.5);
    }

    .tool-block-header {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: baseline;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }

    .tool-block-title {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.45rem;
    }

    .tool-pill {
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      padding: 0.1rem 0.5rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.7);
      background: rgba(249, 250, 251, 0.9);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.09em;
      color: #4b5563;
    }

    .tool-block-body {
      margin-top: 0.35rem;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
    }

    .tool-block-body p {
      margin: 0.1rem 0;
    }

    .prompt-label {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.3rem;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      margin-top: 0.55rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }

    .prompt-label span.dot {
      width: 0.45rem;
      height: 0.45rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: currentColor;
    }

    .prompt-text {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      padding: 0.5rem 0.6rem;
      border-radius: 9px;
      background: #f3f4f6;
      border: 1px dashed #d1d5db;
      font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas,
        "Liberation Mono", "Courier New", monospace;
      white-space: pre-line;
    }

    .note {
      margin-top: 0.9rem;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      padding-left: 0.75rem;
      border-left: 3px solid currentColor;
      color: #374151;
    }

    .note strong {
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    /* Color accents for each column */

    .section-green {
      background: radial-gradient(circle at 0 0, var(--green-light), #ffffff);
      border-top-color: var(--green-strong);
    }

    .section-green .prompt-label,
    .section-green .tool-pill {
      color: var(--green-strong);
    }

    .section-green .prompt-text {
      background: #ecfdf3;
      border-color: rgba(22, 163, 74, 0.25);
    }

    .section-green .note {
      border-left-color: var(--green-strong);
    }

    .section-yellow {
      background: radial-gradient(circle at 0 0, var(--yellow-light), #ffffff);
      border-top-color: var(--yellow-strong);
    }

    .section-yellow .prompt-label,
    .section-yellow .tool-pill {
      color: var(--yellow-strong);
    }

    .section-yellow .prompt-text {
      background: #fffbeb;
      border-color: rgba(234, 179, 8, 0.3);
    }

    .section-yellow .note {
      border-left-color: var(--yellow-strong);
    }

    .section-orange {
      background: radial-gradient(circle at 0 0, var(--orange-light), #ffffff);
      border-top-color: var(--orange-strong);
    }

    .section-orange .prompt-label,
    .section-orange .tool-pill {
      color: var(--orange-strong);
    }

    .section-orange .prompt-text {
      background: #fff7ed;
      border-color: rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.3);
    }

    .section-orange .note {
      border-left-color: var(--orange-strong);
    }

    .section-purple {
      background: radial-gradient(circle at 0 0, var(--purple-light), #ffffff);
      border-top-color: var(--purple-strong);
    }

    .section-purple .prompt-label,
    .section-purple .tool-pill {
      color: var(--purple-strong);
    }

    .section-purple .prompt-text {
      background: #f5f3ff;
      border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.3);
    }

    .section-purple .note {
      border-left-color: var(--purple-strong);
    }

    /* Critical reminder footer */

    footer.critical {
      margin-top: 2.25rem;
      border-radius: 18px;
      padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
      background: #fef3c7;
      border: 1px solid #facc15;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 25px rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.4);
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.85rem;
      align-items: flex-start;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .critical-icon {
      width: 2rem;
      height: 2rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      background: #f97316;
      color: #fffbeb;
      margin-right: 0.2rem;
      flex-shrink: 0;
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 4px rgba(248, 113, 22, 0.35);
    }

    footer.critical strong {
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    footer.critical p {
      margin: 0;
      color: #78350f;
      max-width: 60rem;
    }

    /* Responsive */

    @media (max-width: 960px) {
      .hero-inner {
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.8fr);
      }

      nav.section-nav {
        border-radius: 16px;
      }

      .tool-grid {
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      }

      .teaching-grid {
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 720px) {
      .page {
        padding-inline: 1rem;
      }

      header.hero {
        padding: 1.4rem 1.1rem 1.5rem;
        border-radius: 0 0 24px 24px;
      }

      .hero-inner {
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr);
      }

      .hero-subtitle {
        max-width: 100%;
      }

      nav.section-nav {
        margin-top: 1rem;
      }

      section#getting-started {
        margin-top: 1.7rem;
      }

      .tool-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      .teaching-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      .teaching-section {
        padding-inline: 1.1rem;
      }

      footer.critical {
        border-radius: 16px;
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 400px) {
      header.hero {
        border-radius: 0;
      }

      .hero-title {
        font-size: 1.65rem;
      }

      .hero-subtitle {
        font-size: 0.92rem;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="page">
    <header class="hero">
      <div class="hero-inner">
        <div>
          <div class="hero-eyebrow">
            <span class="dot"></span>
            <span>Teacher’s guide • Free tools</span>
          </div>
          <h1 class="hero-title">
            Teacher’s Guide to Free Google AI Tools
          </h1>
          <p class="hero-subtitle">
            Use Google’s <strong>Gemini chat</strong>, <strong>NotebookLM</strong>, and
            <strong>Gemini in Workspace</strong> as a teaching assistant for planning,
            questioning, and communication. Artificial intelligence (AI) supports your
            work; <strong>you</strong> stay in charge of judgment and instruction.
          </p>
          <p class="hero-disclaimer">
            <strong>Not a replacement for a teacher.</strong>
            Always review, fact‑check, and adapt AI‑generated ideas before using them with
            students or families. Avoid sharing
            <em>Personally Identifiable Information (PII)</em> such as full names,
            addresses, or student ID numbers.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="hero-chip" aria-label="Summary of the three tools">
            <span class="icon" aria-hidden="true">✨</span>
            <div>
              <div><strong>Three free Google tools</strong></div>
              <small>Gemini chat • NotebookLM • Gemini in Gmail/Docs/Slides</small>
            </div>
          </div>

          <nav class="section-nav" aria-label="Jump to teaching uses">
            <ul>
              <li><a href="#generate" class="is-primary"><span class="emoji" aria-hidden="true">📚</span>Generate materials</a></li>
              <li><a href="#questions"><span class="emoji" aria-hidden="true">❓</span>Questions &amp; assessments</a></li>
              <li><a href="#syllabus"><span class="emoji" aria-hidden="true">🧭</span>Syllabus &amp; curriculum</a></li>
              <li><a href="#feedback"><span class="emoji" aria-hidden="true">💬</span>Parent feedback</a></li>
            </ul>
          </nav>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main>
      <!-- Getting started section -->
      <section id="getting-started">
        <h2>Getting started: accessing the free tools</h2>
        <p>
          All of these tools work in a web browser with a Google Account. Availability
          can vary by region and school settings.
        </p>
        <div class="tool-grid">
          <!-- Gemini -->
          <article class="tool-card">
            <h3>
              Google Gemini
              <span class="tool-chip">Chat assistant</span>
            </h3>
            <p class="tool-url">
              Web: <a href="https://gemini.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gemini.google.com</a>
            </p>
            <p class="tool-tagline">Your AI partner for ideas and content.</p>
            <p>
              Start a chat and describe what you need&mdash;lesson plans, examples,
              explanations, or rubrics. You can paste in text from handouts, curricula,
              or standards.
            </p>
          </article>

          <!-- NotebookLM -->
          <article class="tool-card">
            <h3>
              Google NotebookLM
              <span class="tool-chip">Grounded AI</span>
            </h3>
            <p class="tool-url">
              Web: <a href="https://notebooklm.google" target="_blank" rel="noopener">notebooklm.google</a>
            </p>
            <p class="tool-tagline">
              Grounded AI built from <strong>your own sources</strong>.
            </p>
            <p>
              Upload Portable Document Format (PDF) files, Google Docs, slides, or
              copied text to create a custom “notebook”. NotebookLM then answers questions
              and generates materials using only those sources, with citations.
            </p>
          </article>

          <!-- Gemini in Workspace -->
          <article class="tool-card">
            <h3>
              Gemini in Workspace
              <span class="tool-chip">In Docs, Slides &amp; Gmail</span>
            </h3>
            <p class="tool-url">
              Look for the sparkle icon or <strong>Help me write / Help me visualize</strong>.
            </p>
            <p class="tool-tagline">
              Built‑in AI features in Docs, Slides, Gmail, and more.
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Draft or revise emails directly inside Gmail.</li>
              <li>Generate slides, images, and outlines in Google Slides.</li>
              <li>Summarise or rewrite text in Google Docs.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Teaching sections -->
      <section class="teaching-grid" aria-label="Ways teachers can use the tools">
        <!-- 1. Generate teaching materials -->
        <section id="generate" class="teaching-section section-green">
          <div class="teaching-section-inner">
            <div class="section-label">1. Generate teaching materials</div>
            <h2>
              <span class="emoji" aria-hidden="true">📚</span>
              Create lesson plans, handouts &amp; visuals
            </h2>
            <p class="section-tagline">
              Use Gemini and Gemini in Slides to draft structured lessons and
              supporting visuals, then edit like you would any template.
            </p>

            <!-- Tool: Gemini -->
            <article class="tool-block" aria-label="Gemini for teaching materials">
              <div class="tool-block-header">
                <div class="tool-block-title">
                  <span aria-hidden="true">💡</span>
                  <span>Tool: Gemini (chat)</span>
                </div>
                <span class="tool-pill">Content &amp; plans</span>
              </div>
              <div class="tool-block-body">
                <p>
                  Prompt Gemini to generate creative lesson ideas, activity sequences,
                  vocabulary lists, or differentiation suggestions.
                </p>
                <div class="prompt-label">
                  <span class="dot"></span>
                  <span>Example prompt</span>
                </div>
                <p class="prompt-text">
"Create a 5th‑grade lesson plan on photosynthesis with three hands‑on activities and a vocabulary list."
                </p>
              </div>
            </article>

            <!-- Tool: Gemini in Slides -->
            <article class="tool-block" aria-label="Gemini in Slides for teaching materials">
              <div class="tool-block-header">
                <div class="tool-block-title">
                  <span aria-hidden="true">🖼️</span>
                  <span>Tool: Gemini in Slides</span>
                </div>
                <span class="tool-pill">Visuals &amp; images</span>
              </div>
              <div class="tool-block-body">
                <p>
                  In a Google Slides deck, use <strong>Help me visualize</strong> (or the
                  Gemini side panel) to generate images to match your lesson.
                </p>
                <div class="prompt-label">
                  <span class="dot"></span>
                  <span>Example prompt</span>
                </div>
                <p class="prompt-text">
"Generate an image of a futuristic, sustainable city for a history presentation."
                </p>
              </div>
            </article>

            <p class="note">
              <strong>Note:</strong> Treat AI output as a rough draft. Check for
              accuracy, adjust for your students, and make sure examples reflect your
              local curriculum and community.
            </p>
